ions.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20unsure%20which%20direction%20they'd%20take.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20Schaechter%2C%20CEO%20of%20cloud%20cost%20optimization%20firm%20Vantage%2C%20said%20tariffs%20could%20force%20AWS%20to%20tighten%20future%20discounts%20or%20slow%20infrastructure%20growth%20due%20to%20higher%20hardware%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bigger%20threat%2C%20some%20say%2C%20is%20reduced%20cloud%20spending.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BAmazon's%20AWS%20business%20should%20see%20limited%20tariff%20impact%2C%20though%20a%20broader%20economic%20slowdown%20is%20a%20risk%20to%20IT%20spend.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERandall%20Hunt%2C%20CTO%20of%20cloud%20advisory%20firm%20Caylent%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20customers%20are%20already%20cutting%20back%20in%20broad%20spending%20in%20anticipation%20of%20slower%20growth%20and%20rising%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22499984e8-1a37-44c4-a8a3-f5f5e28a20be%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EData%20sovereignty%20and%20Trump-era%20fears%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20uncertainty%20over%20Trump's%20actions%20has%20pushed%20Amazon%20to%20prepare%20for%20even%20more%20extreme%20scenarios%2C%20including%20potential%20US%20government%20demands%20for%20cloud%20customer%20data%20or%20a%20move%20to%20block%20non-US%20users%20from%20accessing%20AWS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20asked%20about%20potential%20US%20government%20data%20requests%2C%20Amazon%20instructed%20employees%20to%20emphasize%20that%20AWS%20does%20not%20disclose%20customer%20information%20unless%20legally%20required%20and%20that%20all%20requests%20are%20thoroughly%20reviewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20guidance%20also%20clarifies%20AWS's%20position%20on%20the%20CLOUD%20Act%2C%20or%20Clarifying%20Lawful%20Overseas%20Use%20of%20Data%20Act.%20The%20CLOUD%20Act%2C%20passed%20in%202018%2C%20gives%20US%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20the%20authority%20to%20access%20data%20held%20by%20US-based%20companies%2C%20even%20if%20stored%20abroad.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAWS%20has%20not%20provided%20enterprise%20or%20government%20customer%20data%20stored%20outside%20the%20US%20since%20at%20least%202020%20and%20it%20will%20challenge%20any%20%26quot%3Bover-broad%26quot%3B%20or%20unlawful%20requests%2C%20the%20document%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20CLOUD%20Act%20does%20not%20provide%20the%20U.S.%20government%20with%20unfettered%20access%20to%20data%20held%20by%20cloud%20providers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22trump%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679bf5727bb3f854015b42f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump.%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20Trump%20could%20block%20foreign%20access%20to%20AWS%2C%20the%20document%20stops%20short%20of%20addressing%20whether%20the%20president%20has%20the%20authority%2C%20but%20notes%20there's%20no%20indication%20such%20action%20is%20imminent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20it%20argues%20that%20doing%20so%20would%20contradict%20the%20administration's%20stated%20goal%20of%20supporting%20US%20tech%20companies%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAWS%20is%20closely%20plugged%20into%20US%20policy%20and%20this%20Administration's%20efforts%2C%20and%20can%20confirm%20we%20have%20heard%20nothing%20about%20restricting%20cloud%20services%20to%20non-US%20customers%20in%20response%20to%20addressing%20trade%20imbalances%20or%20unfair%20trade%20barriers%2C%20and%20expect%20their%20focus%20to%20continue%20to%20be%20on%20tariffs%20as%20the%20'rebalancing'%20mechanism%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2234f7587b-bb27-4251-9fde-2fbae1bcea41%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESanctions%20and%20'Buy%20Canada'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAWS%20also%20addresses%20fears%20that%20US%20sanctions%20could%20restrict%20access%20to%20its%20services%20in%20certain%20countries.%20The%20guidance%20notes%20that%20full%20country-wide%20sanctions%20are%20rare%20and%20that%20in%20the%20past%2C%20companies%20have%20been%20given%20time%20to%20wind%20down%20operations%20when%20sanctions%20do%20occur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUS%20country-wide%20sanctions%20or%20services%20restrictions%20are%20exceedingly%20rare%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20in%20the%20theoretical%20case%20that%20such%20sanctions%20ever%20came%20to%20pass%2C%20AWS%20would%20do%20everything%20practically%20possible%20to%20provide%20continuity%20of%20service.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20AWS%20is%20preparing%20for%20patriotic%20backlash%20in%20some%20markets%2C%20such%20as%20a%20potential%20%26quot%3BBuy%20Canada%26quot%3B%20movement.%20Employees%20are%20told%20to%20clarify%20that%20AWS's%20Canada%20office%20is%20a%20registered%20Canadian%20corporation%20headquartered%20in%20Toronto%2C%20and%20that%20customers%20can%20choose%20to%20store%20their%20data%20locally%20and%20encrypt%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20guidance%20urges%20caution.%20Employees%20should%20be%20careful%20framing%20AWS%20as%20a%20%26quot%3BCanadian%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20given%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20AWS%20is%20a%20'Canadian%20business'%20will%20depend%20on%20how%20that%20is%20defined%20in%20particular%20circumstances%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20concludes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aekim%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eekim%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%2C%20Telegram%2C%20or%20WhatsApp%20at%20650-942-3061.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fins